Two people died and another two were seriously injured during a shooting in Pietermaritzburg. On Friday morning, unknown gunmen opened fire at a group of men at the corner of West and Church streets, said provincial police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala. "Two people were declared dead at the scene while the other two sustained injuries and were taken to hospital for medical attention. The motive for the killing is yet to be established as investigations unfolds," she said. Gwala said two charges of murder and two of attempted murder were opened at Pietermaritzburg SAPS for investigation.